snippet.textDisplay: So.... seeing the added customization features of this "gaming browser" made me wonder why the heck we got a gaming browser before an artist or creatives browser. Which.... would mostly be a browser so pumped full of customization options that most normal people wouldn't have the patience to deal with it, but us creative types could have a field day with it. And you know, maybe some really nice features like baked-in media posting, so that I can just upload my work once and have it go to all of the platforms I use simultaneously. And probably also a baked-in color picker. The pop-out media thing would be nice there too, and make more sense because because you can have educational content (and drawing references) up without having to obscure the canvas.
